==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic عبد (abd = servant) + ال (al = 'the'). The [[article]] ال (al) often [[assimilate]] with epitheta beginning with '''r''' and '''s'''.

===Proper noun===
'''Abdul'''
#a male [[Muslim]] [[given name]]
#Arabic for "servant of the" one of 100 names [[epitheta]] for Allah. By example: [[Abdullatif]]. Both the [[epithetum]] [[Latif]] = 'the Beautiful' as the whole name [[Abdullatif]] are given to [[Muslim]] man. Women get only the female form [[Latifa]] of one of [[Allah]]'s epitheta. (It should be followed by another word to form a complete name. If that name is [[Muslim]], the added word would be a word describing [[Allah]].)

